Marketing Brief -- Planned Parenthood Federation:
   Wattleton, Abortion Rights
   Advocate, Quits as President
Ms. Wattleton, 48 years old, was hired as executive
director of the Planned Parenthood affiliate in Dayton, Ohio,
in 1970. Eight years later, at 34, she was chosen to head the
national organization. Under Ms. Wattleton, Planned
Parenthood became one of the most forceful abortion-rights
advocates. It has 900 clinics and a budget of more than $300
million.